    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Update on the creme fraiche!  I&#8217;ve done a bit of research around the Web and have found a number of sources that mention that you must heat the whipping cream to roughly &#8220;wrist temperature&#8221; (100 degrees Fahrenheit or so) before adding the buttermilk.  And it could take anywhere between 12 and 36 hours at room temperature to achieve a good, thick consistency.  Pipstar et al., hope that helps&#8230;</p>
    </div>

